ntity, for better and for worse. Tentler draws on evidence from pastoral literature, sermons, lay writings, private correspondence, and interviews with fifty-six priests ordained between 1938 and 1968, concluding, "the recent history of American Catholicism. can only be understood by taking birth control into account."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aBirth controlxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 0aBirth controlzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aContraceptionxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 0aContraceptionzUnited StatesxHistory. 4aReligious Studies. 4aU.S. History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172667540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501726675423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501726675/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles